{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place butter, milk, yoghurt, oil, egg, banana and honey in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add plain flour, wholemeal flour, oats, bran, almonds, bicarbonate of soda and salt then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Set aside to rest in mixing bowl for 15 minutes.","Heat oil in a large non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. Pour small ladlefuls of batter into pan and fry for 1-2 minutes or until bubbles form on top. Turn over and cook for a further 1 minute, then remove and keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter.","Serve pancakes warm with maple syrup or yoghurt and fresh fruit."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 g unsalted butter, soft","240 g semi-skimmed milk","60 g fat-free plain yoghurt","10 g groundnut oil, plus extra for frying","1 large egg","1 banana, very ripe, cut in pieces","1 Tbsp honey","60 g plain flour","60 g wholemeal flour","25 g rolled oats","3 Tbsp wheat bran","2 Tbsp flaked almonds","1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","½ tsp fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r282117","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-D6q0ndhuLCI\/XZaeqHcC4lI\/AAAAAAAAgns\/cyMsegeAW4MUfltCqT-Z5uEcSBwXxo0TACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0__rKPV2Ti8AaJ5Lx2.png","title":"Multigrain Banana Pancakes","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.6 g","fat":"3.5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"13 g","calories":"425 kJ \/ 101 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large non-stick frying pan, small ladle, fish slice, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Lazy Sunday mornings are the perfect time to enjoy a big stack of homemade pancakes. With slow-releasing oats and nutrient-rich almonds, this healthier version includes bananas for natural sweetness. For a special treat, serve with lashings of maple syrup!"],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","12 pieces"]}